 PERUGIA, Oct. 19 (Xinhua) -- The 27th international chocolate festival "Eurochocolate" kicked off on October 15th in Perugia, an Italian city with a tradition of chocolate production. The ten-day event presented different kinds of chocolate products and offered a variety of activities including chocolate making class, chocolate tasting and performances. A cook makes chocolate during the 27th Eurochocolate in Perugia, Italy, Oct. 15, 2021. (Xinhua/Jin Mamengni)  People buy chocolate products during the 27th Eurochocolate in Perugia, Italy, Oct. 15, 2021. (Xinhua/Jin Mamengni)  An exhibitor takes a piece of chocolate during the 27th Eurochocolate in Perugia, Italy, Oct. 15, 2021. (Xinhua/Jin Mamengni)  An exhibitor displays a large piece of chocolate during the 27th Eurochocolate in Perugia, Italy, Oct. 15, 2021. (Xinhua/Jin Mamengni) Produced by Xinhua Global Serviceâ–  